In what was one of his first official functions, the new Japan ambassador Toshitsugu Uesawa hosted a party at his residence in Nairobi on Tuesday evening. The occasion was to celebrate the Japan Self-Defense Forces day, an annual event commemorating the formation of the country s Self-Defense Forces.The event was marked with a range of activities including the showcasing of martial arts.Present was Zimbabwean ambassador Kelebert Nkomani, the Moipei family among many others.